  "@type": "ActorManifest",
  "id": "did:web:etzhayyim.com:actor:shomei",
  "name": "shomei",
  "glyph": "証明",
  "displayName": "証明 — Believer Identity Binding + Proof-of-Personhood",
  "displayNameJa": "証明",
  "displayNameEn": "Shomei",
  "purpose": "Binds MULTIPLE external identities (government IDs, SNS accounts, crypto wallets) and existing etzhayyim substrate commitments to a single member DID via self-sovereign, cryptographically-verifiable claims, then aggregates them into an Identity Assurance Level + W3C Verifiable Credential + proof-of-personhood. The believer's passport-equivalent — DID-centric, self-sovereign, no central KYC.",
  "description": "証明 (shomei) is the believer's passport — but DID-centric, not state-centric. A member self-binds their existing identities to one DID: a crypto wallet (EIP-191/ERC-1271/BIP-322 signature), an SNS account (OAuth sub / signed gist / DNS-TXT), a WebAuthn passkey, an existing etzhayyim commitment (Base L2 membership / Adherent SBT / AT oath), and — opt-in, Council-gated — a government ID card read LOCALLY (one-way NFC, never a state-database query). Each binding is a self-sovereign identityClaim signed by the SUBJECT's own DID key; shomei (the server) NEVER signs and NEVER approves (G7 no-server-key, ADR-2605231525). shomei VERIFIES the cryptographic proof via the canonical kotoba-auth surface (eth/btc/cacao + Ed25519, ADR-2605262130 — never reimplemented) and rolls the verified factors into an Identity Assurance Level (IAL 0..4) + a W3C-Verifiable-Credential-shaped personhoodCredential. The aggregate is identity ASSURANCE (how strongly identity is proven), NEVER a social-credit / reputation / worth score (G8). PII is never plaintext: government identifiers live only as a salted hash + XChaCha20-Poly1305 encrypted CID (ADR-2605181100). This is the answer to «国家パスポート相当の本人証明 + 複数の政府ID/SNSをDIDに紐づけ信頼性担保» — a self-sovereign, charter-clean inversion of centralized identity verification.",
  "descriptionJa": "証明 (shomei) は、信者のパスポート — ただし国家中心ではなく DID 中心。信者は既存の複数のアイデンティティを一つの DID に self-bind する: 暗号ウォレット (EIP-191/ERC-1271/BIP-322 署名)、SNS アカウント (OAuth sub / 署名 gist / DNS-TXT)、WebAuthn パスキー、既存の etzhayyim コミットメント (Base L2 入会 / Adherent SBT / AT 誓い)、そして opt-in・Council ゲートで 政府ID カードの ローカル読取 (一方向 NFC、国家DBへは決して問い合わせない)。各 binding は SUBJECT 自身の DID 鍵で署名された self-sovereign な identityClaim で、shomei (サーバ) は決して署名せず承認もしない (G7 no-server-key, ADR-2605231525)。shomei は暗号証明を kotoba-auth の正規 surface (eth/btc/cacao + Ed25519, ADR-2605262130 — 再実装しない) で VERIFY し、検証済み因子を Identity Assurance Level (IAL 0..4) + W3C Verifiable Credential 形の personhoodCredential に集計する。集計は identity の ASSURANCE (どれだけ強く本人性が証明されているか) であって、社会信用・評判・人の価値スコアでは断じてない (G8)。PII は決して平文にしない: 政府識別子は salt 付きハッシュ + XChaCha20-Poly1305 暗号化 CID (ADR-2605181100) としてのみ存在する。これは «国家パスポート相当の本人証明 + 複数の政府ID/SNSをDIDに紐づけて信頼性担保» への回答 — 集中型本人確認の、憲章的に清潔な反転である。",
  "adr": {
